Neutral votes are valid. Think of it as up voting it for one reason, but down voting it for another. In this case, I would up vote it for being well written, but down vote it for the usage of a well known pop culture icon/group.

In the latter part, think of it as if you were voting for someone in an election because they are associated or supported by your favorite actor. Was your vote swayed by the presence of the actor? Or was it swayed because you supported the person you're voting for?

However, my stance is that I don't think the author intended for this type of effect. It was just an unfortunate and unexpected side effect. The intent was good, to make something funny, and to a degree they achieved it. It's just raising questions now is all.

Anyways, I'm analyzing into this way too much, and it's getting late for me. I need to stop or I might go even deeper, and trust me, I can think about stuff quite deeply if I want to.







